1
00:00:44,866 --> 00:00:48,119
Once upon a time
in a faraway land

2
00:00:48,161 --> 00:00:51,789
a young prince lived
in a shining castle.

3
00:00:51,873 --> 00:00:55,293
Although he had
everything his heart desired

4
00:00:55,334 --> 00:01:00,214
the prince was spoiled,
selfish and unkind.

5
00:01:00,256 --> 00:01:02,508
But then, one winter's night

6
00:01:02,549 --> 00:01:05,677
an old beggar woman
came to the castle

7
00:01:05,719 --> 00:01:08,221
and offered him a single rose

8
00:01:08,263 --> 00:01:11,849
in return for shelter
from the bitter cold.

9
00:01:11,975 --> 00:01:14,435
Repulsed by
her haggard appearance

10
00:01:14,477 --> 00:01:19,148
the prince sneered at the gift
and turned the old woman away

11
00:01:19,190 --> 00:01:23,151
but she warned him not to be
deceived by appearances

12
00:01:23,193 --> 00:01:25,195
for beauty is found within

13
00:01:25,237 --> 00:01:27,656
and when he dismissed her again

14
00:01:27,739 --> 00:01:30,575
the old woman's ugliness
melted away

15
00:01:30,617 --> 00:01:33,202
to reveal
a beautiful enchantress.

16
00:01:33,244 --> 00:01:36,664
The prince tried to apologize,
but it was too late

17
00:01:36,706 --> 00:01:40,209
for she had seen that there was
no love in his heart

18
00:01:40,251 --> 00:01:42,836
and as punishment,
she transformed him

19
00:01:42,836 --> 00:01:44,338
into a hideous beast

20
00:01:44,421 --> 00:01:47,549
and placed a powerful spell
on the castle

21
00:01:47,591 --> 00:01:49,426
and all who lived there.

22
00:01:49,467 --> 00:01:51,761
Ashamed of his monstrous form

23
00:01:51,803 --> 00:01:55,181
the Beast concealed himself
inside his castle

24
00:01:55,223 --> 00:01:58,184
with a magic mirror
as his only window

25
00:01:58,225 --> 00:01:59,810
to the outside world.

26
00:01:59,852 --> 00:02:04,773
The rose she had offered
was truly an enchanted rose

27
00:02:04,815 --> 00:02:08,360
which would bloom
until his 21st year.

28
00:02:08,401 --> 00:02:11,154
lf he could learn
to love another

29
00:02:11,196 --> 00:02:16,117
and earn her love in return
by the time the last petal fell

30
00:02:16,200 --> 00:02:19,078
then the spell would be broken.

31
00:02:19,119 --> 00:02:24,374
lf not, he would be doomed
to remain a beast for all time.

32
00:02:26,293 --> 00:02:30,338
As the years passed,
he fell into despair

33
00:02:30,380 --> 00:02:33,341
and lost all hope

34
00:02:33,383 --> 00:02:37,386
for who could ever learn
to love a beast?

35
00:03:03,118 --> 00:03:08,248
Little town,
it's a quiet village

36
00:03:08,290 --> 00:03:12,877
Every day lile the one before

37
00:03:12,919 --> 00:03:17,214
Little town,
full of little people

38
00:03:17,256 --> 00:03:22,594
Waking up... to... say...

39
00:03:22,636 --> 00:03:23,512
Bonjour!

40
00:03:23,512 --> 00:03:24,346
- Bonjour!

41
00:03:24,388 --> 00:03:25,305
- Bonjour!
- Bonjour!

42
00:03:25,347 --> 00:03:25,889
Bonjour!

43
00:03:25,931 --> 00:03:27,515
There goes the baker

44
00:03:27,515 --> 00:03:30,310
With his tray like always

45
00:03:30,351 --> 00:03:33,396
The same old bread
and rolls to sell

46
00:03:33,438 --> 00:03:35,231
Every morning just the same

47
00:03:35,231 --> 00:03:36,691
Since the morning that we came

48
00:03:36,774 --> 00:03:38,359
To this poor provincial town...

49
00:03:38,400 --> 00:03:39,360
Good morning, Belle.

50
00:03:39,401 --> 00:03:40,319
Good morning, Monsieur.

51
00:03:40,361 --> 00:03:41,320
Where are you off to?

52
00:03:41,362 --> 00:03:42,237
The bookshop.

53
00:03:42,279 --> 00:03:44,406
l just finished
the most wonderful story

54
00:03:44,489 --> 00:03:46,241
about a beanstalk
and an ogre, and...

55
00:03:46,283 --> 00:03:47,367
That's nice.

56
00:03:47,409 --> 00:03:48,618
Marie! The baguettes.

57
00:03:48,618 --> 00:03:50,078
Hurry up!

58
00:03:50,120 --> 00:03:51,037
Look, there she goes

59
00:03:51,079 --> 00:03:53,456
The girl is strange, no question

60
00:03:53,498 --> 00:03:56,751
Dazed and distracted,
can't you tell?

61
00:03:56,834 --> 00:03:58,544
Never part of any crowd

62
00:03:58,544 --> 00:04:00,337
'Cause her head's
up on some cloud

63
00:04:00,379 --> 00:04:04,174
No denying she's a funny girl,
that Belle

64
00:04:04,174 --> 00:04:05,300
Bonjour

65
00:04:05,342 --> 00:04:06,259
Good day

66
00:04:06,301 --> 00:04:07,969
How is your family?

67
00:04:08,011 --> 00:04:08,928
Bonjour

68
00:04:08,970 --> 00:04:09,888
Good day

69
00:04:09,971 --> 00:04:11,723
How is your wife?

70
00:04:11,848 --> 00:04:13,558
l need six eggs

71
00:04:13,599 --> 00:04:15,017
That's too expensive

72
00:04:15,059 --> 00:04:19,146
There must be more
than this provincial life...

73
00:04:19,188 --> 00:04:20,606
Ah, Belle.

74
00:04:20,648 --> 00:04:21,607
Good morning.

75
00:04:21,648 --> 00:04:23,400
l've come to return
the book l borrowed.

76
00:04:23,442 --> 00:04:24,359
Finished already?

77
00:04:24,401 --> 00:04:25,652
Oh, l couldn't put it down.

78
00:04:25,736 --> 00:04:27,571
Have you got anything new?

79
00:04:27,654 --> 00:04:28,697
Not since yesterday.

80
00:04:28,738 --> 00:04:29,989
That's all right.

81
00:04:30,031 --> 00:04:31,950
l'll borrow... this one.

82
00:04:31,991 --> 00:04:32,992
That one?

83
00:04:33,034 --> 00:04:34,410
But you've read it twice.

84
00:04:34,452 --> 00:04:36,579
Well, it's my favorite--
far-off places

85
00:04:36,621 --> 00:04:37,913
daring sword fights

86
00:04:37,955 --> 00:04:39,748
magic spells,
a prince in disguise.

87
00:04:39,748 --> 00:04:42,793
lf you like it
all that much, it's yours.

88
00:04:42,835 --> 00:04:44,795
-But, sir...
-l insist.

89
00:04:44,878 --> 00:04:45,754
Well, thank you.

90
00:04:45,879 --> 00:04:47,005
Thank you very much.

91
00:04:47,047 --> 00:04:48,548
Look, there she goes

92
00:04:48,590 --> 00:04:51,050
That girl is so peculiar

93
00:04:51,092 --> 00:04:54,262
l wonder if she's feeling well

94
00:04:54,303 --> 00:04:56,013
With a dreamy, far-off look

95
00:04:56,055 --> 00:04:57,681
And her nose stuck in a book

96
00:04:57,723 --> 00:05:01,643
What a puzzle to the rest
of us is Belle

97
00:05:01,685 --> 00:05:07,399
Oh, isn't this amazing?

98
00:05:07,440 --> 00:05:16,407
lt's my favorite part
because you'll see

99
00:05:16,532 --> 00:05:22,371
Here's where she meets
Prince Charming

100
00:05:22,412 --> 00:05:25,999
But she won't discover
that it's him

101
00:05:26,041 --> 00:05:29,294
Till Chapter Three

102
00:05:29,335 --> 00:05:31,254
Hey! Hey! Hey! Hey! Hey!

103
00:05:31,296 --> 00:05:34,674
Now, it's no wonder
that her name means beauty

104
00:05:34,757 --> 00:05:37,760
Her looks have got no parallel

105
00:05:37,802 --> 00:05:39,595
But behind that fair facade

106
00:05:39,637 --> 00:05:41,638
l'm afraid she's rather odd

107
00:05:41,680 --> 00:05:43,557
Very different
from the rest of us

108
00:05:43,599 --> 00:05:45,350
She's nothing like
the rest of us

109
00:05:45,350 --> 00:05:49,104
Yes, different
from the rest of us is Belle

110
00:05:53,691 --> 00:05:55,568
Wow, you didn't miss
a shot, Gaston.

111
00:05:55,610 --> 00:05:56,610
You're the greatest hunter

112
00:05:56,652 --> 00:05:57,820
in the whole world.

113
00:05:57,862 --> 00:05:59,405
l know.

114
00:05:59,446 --> 00:06:01,323
No beast alive
stands a chance against you

115
00:06:01,365 --> 00:06:03,200
and no girl, for that matter.

116
00:06:03,242 --> 00:06:04,159
lt's true, Lefou

117
00:06:04,201 --> 00:06:06,536
and l've got my sights set
on that one.

118
00:06:06,578 --> 00:06:08,204
The inventor's daughter?

119
00:06:08,330 --> 00:06:10,915
She's the one-- the lucky girl
l'm going to marry.

120
00:06:10,957 --> 00:06:11,958
But, she...

121
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:13,292
The most beautiful girl in town.

122
00:06:13,292 --> 00:06:14,418
l know, but...

123
00:06:14,460 --> 00:06:16,128
That makes her the best

124
00:06:16,170 --> 00:06:17,755
and don't l deserve the best?

125
00:06:17,797 --> 00:06:18,797
Well, of course.

126
00:06:18,881 --> 00:06:20,007
l mean, you do, but...

127
00:06:20,049 --> 00:06:23,135
Right from the moment
when l met her, saw her

128
00:06:23,177 --> 00:06:23,260
l said, ''She's gorgeous,''
and l fell

129
00:06:23,260 --> 00:06:26,888
l said, ''She's gorgeous,''
and l fell

130
00:06:26,930 --> 00:06:30,767
Here in town there's only she
who is beautiful as me

131
00:06:30,809 --> 00:06:34,687
So, l'm making plans
to woo and marry Belle

132
00:06:34,729 --> 00:06:38,441
Look, there he goes,
isn't he dreamy?

133
00:06:38,482 --> 00:06:41,443
Monsieur Gaston,
oh, he's so cute

134
00:06:41,485 --> 00:06:44,988
Be still, my heart,
l'm hardly breathing

135
00:06:45,030 --> 00:06:48,366
He's such a tall, dark,
strong and handsome brute

136
00:06:48,408 --> 00:06:50,618
-Bonjour -Pardon
-Good day -Mais oui

137
00:06:50,660 --> 00:06:52,495
-You call this bacon?
-What lovely grapes

138
00:06:52,537 --> 00:06:54,205
-Ten yards -Some cheese
-'Scuse me -One pound

139
00:06:54,247 --> 00:06:55,164
l'll get the knife

140
00:06:55,206 --> 00:06:56,123
Please let me through

141
00:06:56,123 --> 00:06:57,166
-This bread -Those fish

142
00:06:57,208 --> 00:06:58,125
-lt's stale -They smell

143
00:06:58,167 --> 00:06:59,084
Madame's mistaken

144
00:06:59,126 --> 00:07:00,294
There must be more

145
00:07:00,336 --> 00:07:02,838
Than this provincial life

146
00:07:02,838 --> 00:07:06,383
Just watch, l'm going
to make Belle my wife

147
00:07:06,424 --> 00:07:07,384
Look, there she goes

148
00:07:07,384 --> 00:07:09,969
A girl who's strange
but special

149
00:07:10,011 --> 00:07:13,181
A most peculiar mademoiselle

150
00:07:13,222 --> 00:07:14,682
lt's a pity and a sin

151
00:07:14,724 --> 00:07:16,392
She doesn't quite fit in

152
00:07:16,517 --> 00:07:18,102
'Cause she really is
a funny girl

153
00:07:18,102 --> 00:07:20,312
A beauty but a funny girl

154
00:07:20,354 --> 00:07:25,150
She really is a funny girl

155
00:07:25,192 --> 00:07:28,194
That Belle...

156
00:07:28,236 --> 00:07:31,114
Bonjour, bonjour.

157
00:07:34,158 --> 00:07:35,368
Hello, Belle.

158
00:07:35,409 --> 00:07:36,994
Bonjour, Gaston.

159
00:07:37,036 --> 00:07:39,079
Gaston,
may l have my book, please?

160
00:07:39,121 --> 00:07:40,205
How can you read this?

161
00:07:40,247 --> 00:07:41,331
There's no pictures.

162
00:07:41,373 --> 00:07:43,333
Well, some people
use their imagination.

163
00:07:43,375 --> 00:07:45,377
Belle, it's about time
you got your head

164
00:07:45,419 --> 00:07:46,336
out of those books

165
00:07:46,378 --> 00:07:49,005
and paid attention
to more important things...

166
00:07:49,089 --> 00:07:50,006
like me.

167
00:07:52,008 --> 00:07:54,302
The whole town's
talking about it.

168
00:07:54,343 --> 00:07:56,262
lt's not right
for a woman to read.

169
00:07:56,304 --> 00:07:58,973
Soon she starts getting ideas,
and thinking...

170
00:07:59,014 --> 00:08:00,432
Gaston,
you are positively primeval.

171
00:08:00,474 --> 00:08:01,600
Why, thank you, Belle.

172
00:08:01,642 --> 00:08:04,603
What do you say you and me
take a walk over to the tavern

173
00:08:04,645 --> 00:08:06,229
and take a look at my trophies?

174
00:08:06,271 --> 00:08:07,981
Maybe some other time.

175
00:08:08,023 --> 00:08:09,107
What's wrong with her?

176
00:08:09,149 --> 00:08:10,066
She's crazy.

177
00:08:10,108 --> 00:08:11,609
He's gorgeous.

178
00:08:11,651 --> 00:08:12,985
Please, Gaston, l can't.

179
00:08:13,027 --> 00:08:15,071
l have to get home
to help my father.

180
00:08:15,112 --> 00:08:16,072
Good-bye.

181
00:08:16,072 --> 00:08:17,573
That crazy old loon--

182
00:08:17,615 --> 00:08:19,909
he needs all the
help he can get.

183
00:08:19,909 --> 00:08:22,453
Don't talk about my father
that way.

184
00:08:22,536 --> 00:08:25,038
Yeah, don't talk
about her father that way.

185
00:08:25,080 --> 00:08:26,456
My father is not crazy.

186
00:08:26,498 --> 00:08:27,457
He's a genius.

187
00:08:31,085 --> 00:08:32,295
Ooh!

188
00:08:40,219 --> 00:08:41,845
Papa?

189
00:08:41,887 --> 00:08:44,222
How on earth did that happen?

190
00:08:44,264 --> 00:08:45,682
Doggone it!

191
00:08:45,724 --> 00:08:47,475
Are you all right, Papa?

192
00:08:47,517 --> 00:08:51,104
l'm about ready to give
up on this hunk of junk.

193
00:08:51,145 --> 00:08:52,897
You always say that.

194
00:08:52,897 --> 00:08:54,023
l mean it this time.

195
00:08:54,065 --> 00:08:54,941
l'll never get

196
00:08:54,982 --> 00:08:57,234
this boneheaded contraption
to work!

197
00:08:57,276 --> 00:08:58,360
Yes, you will

198
00:08:58,402 --> 00:09:00,654
and you'll win first prize
at the fair tomorrow.

199
00:09:00,696 --> 00:09:01,572
Humph!

200
00:09:01,613 --> 00:09:04,449
And become
a world-famous inventor.

201
00:09:04,449 --> 00:09:06,368
You really believe that?

202
00:09:06,368 --> 00:09:07,827
l always have.

203
00:09:07,869 --> 00:09:09,871
Well, what are we waiting for?

204
00:09:09,913 --> 00:09:12,457
l'll have this thing fixed
in no time.

205
00:09:12,498 --> 00:09:13,833
Hand me that, uh...

206
00:09:13,875 --> 00:09:15,543
dog-legged clincher, there.

207
00:09:15,585 --> 00:09:18,254
So, did you have a
good time in town today?

208
00:09:18,337 --> 00:09:20,297
l got a new book.

209
00:09:20,339 --> 00:09:23,592
Papa, do you think l'm odd?

210
00:09:23,634 --> 00:09:24,843
My daughter? Odd?

211
00:09:24,885 --> 00:09:27,679
Where would you get
an idea like that?

212
00:09:27,679 --> 00:09:28,763
Oh, l don't know.

213
00:09:28,805 --> 00:09:31,516
lt's just that l'm not sure
l fit in here.

214
00:09:31,558 --> 00:09:33,935
There's no one
l can really talk to.

215
00:09:33,976 --> 00:09:35,645
What about that Gaston?

216
00:09:35,686 --> 00:09:37,313
He's a handsome fellow.

217
00:09:37,355 --> 00:09:40,983
He's handsome, all right,
and rude, and conceited, and...

218
00:09:41,025 --> 00:09:42,734
Oh, Papa, he's not for me.

219
00:09:42,776 --> 00:09:44,069
Well, don't you worry

220
00:09:44,111 --> 00:09:46,947
'cause this invention's
going to be the start

221
00:09:46,988 --> 00:09:48,365
of a new life for us.

222
00:09:48,406 --> 00:09:49,824
l think that's done it.

223
00:09:49,866 --> 00:09:51,576
Now, let's give it a try.

224
00:10:05,297 --> 00:10:06,548
lt works!

225
00:10:06,590 --> 00:10:08,800
lt does?

226
00:10:08,842 --> 00:10:09,968
lt does!

227
00:10:10,009 --> 00:10:10,927
You did it!

228
00:10:10,969 --> 00:10:12,136
You really did it!

229
00:10:12,178 --> 00:10:13,888
Hitch up Philippe, girl.

230
00:10:13,930 --> 00:10:15,598
l'm off to the fair!

231
00:10:17,516 --> 00:10:18,726
Good-bye, Papa.

232
00:10:18,767 --> 00:10:20,060
Good luck.

233
00:10:20,102 --> 00:10:23,105
Good-bye, Belle,
and take care while l'm gone.

234
00:10:40,329 --> 00:10:41,288
We should be there by now.

235
00:10:41,288 --> 00:10:42,206
We should be there by now.

236
00:10:42,247 --> 00:10:44,374
Maybe we've missed the turn.

237
00:10:44,416 --> 00:10:46,251
l guess l should have taken...

238
00:10:46,251 --> 00:10:47,627
Wait a minute.

239
00:10:51,589 --> 00:10:53,758
Let's go this way.

240
00:11:04,101 --> 00:11:05,977
Come on, Philippe,
it's a shortcut.

241
00:11:06,019 --> 00:11:07,479
We'll be there in no time.

242
00:11:25,495 --> 00:11:27,038
This can't be right.

243
00:11:27,080 --> 00:11:29,582
Where have you taken us,
Philippe?

244
00:11:29,624 --> 00:11:32,293
We'd better turn around.

245
00:11:33,753 --> 00:11:35,129
Whoa...

246
00:11:35,171 --> 00:11:37,465
Whoa, boy, whoa, whoa, Philippe.

247
00:11:38,757 --> 00:11:40,342
Oh...!

248
00:11:40,342 --> 00:11:41,927
Oh, look out!

249
00:11:45,722 --> 00:11:47,265
Whoa!

250
00:11:47,307 --> 00:11:49,184
Whoa, boy!

251
00:11:49,225 --> 00:11:51,936
Back up, back up, back up!

252
00:11:51,978 --> 00:11:53,938
Good boy, good boy.

253
00:11:53,980 --> 00:11:54,981
That's it.

254
00:11:55,022 --> 00:11:56,023
Back up!

255
00:11:56,065 --> 00:11:57,650
Steady, steady.

256
00:11:57,691 --> 00:11:58,943
Now, steady.

257
00:12:00,986 --> 00:12:02,779
Philippe, no!

258
00:12:08,451 --> 00:12:09,786
Philippe.

259
00:12:12,497 --> 00:12:14,248
Oh...

260
00:12:34,475 --> 00:12:36,394
Help!

261
00:12:36,394 --> 00:12:38,646
ls someone there?!

262
00:12:44,276 --> 00:12:45,819
Oh!

263
00:13:05,045 --> 00:13:07,339
What...?

264
00:13:07,380 --> 00:13:10,300
Oh...

265
00:13:13,845 --> 00:13:15,805
Hello?

266
00:13:17,807 --> 00:13:19,266
Hello?

267
00:13:19,308 --> 00:13:22,561
Poor fellow, must have
lost his way in the woods.

268
00:13:22,603 --> 00:13:24,688
Keep quiet; maybe he'll go away.

269
00:13:24,730 --> 00:13:26,940
ls someone there?

270
00:13:26,982 --> 00:13:30,527
Not a word, Lumiere;
not one word.

271
00:13:30,610 --> 00:13:34,322
l don't mean to intrude,
but l've lost my horse

272
00:13:34,363 --> 00:13:37,533
and l need a place to stay
for the night.

273
00:13:37,575 --> 00:13:39,493
Oh, Cogsworth, have a heart.

