00:36:29,749 --> 00:36:30,792
Well, keep it down.

828
00:36:30,833 --> 00:36:32,710
lf the master finds out
about this

829
00:36:32,794 --> 00:36:33,920
it will be our necks.

830
00:36:33,961 --> 00:36:36,172
Of course, of course.

831
00:36:36,213 --> 00:36:38,883
But what is dinner
without a little music?

832
00:36:38,924 --> 00:36:40,759
Music?

833
00:36:40,801 --> 00:36:43,470
Ma chere
mademoiselle.

834
00:36:43,512 --> 00:36:47,557
lt is with deepest pride
and greatest pleasure

835
00:36:47,557 --> 00:36:49,642
that we welcome you tonight.

836
00:36:49,684 --> 00:36:50,852
And now we invite you to relax.

837
00:36:50,852 --> 00:36:51,769
And now we invite you to relax.

838
00:36:51,894 --> 00:36:53,354
Let us pull up a chair

839
00:36:53,396 --> 00:36:55,982
as the dining room
proudly presents...

840
00:36:56,023 --> 00:36:57,942
your dinner.

841
00:36:59,568 --> 00:37:02,112
Be... our... guest

842
00:37:02,154 --> 00:37:03,530
Be our guest

843
00:37:03,572 --> 00:37:06,449
Put our service to the test

844
00:37:06,491 --> 00:37:08,243
Tie your napkin 'round
your neck, cherie

845
00:37:08,284 --> 00:37:10,787
And we provide the rest

846
00:37:10,828 --> 00:37:13,206
Soup du jour,
Hot hors d'oeuvres

847
00:37:13,289 --> 00:37:15,041
Why, we only live to serve

848
00:37:15,082 --> 00:37:16,459
Try the gray stuff

849
00:37:16,500 --> 00:37:17,585
lt's delicious

850
00:37:17,626 --> 00:37:19,753
Don't believe me, ask the dishes

851
00:37:19,795 --> 00:37:21,880
They can sing, they can dance

852
00:37:21,922 --> 00:37:24,174
After all, Miss, this is France

853
00:37:24,216 --> 00:37:28,094
And a dinner here
is never second best

854
00:37:28,136 --> 00:37:30,471
Go on, unfold your menu

855
00:37:30,513 --> 00:37:32,557
Take a glance and then

856
00:37:32,598 --> 00:37:33,558
You'll be our guest

857
00:37:33,599 --> 00:37:34,767
Oui, our guest

858
00:37:34,809 --> 00:37:36,686
Be our guest

859
00:37:36,769 --> 00:37:38,979
Beef ragout, cheese souffle

860
00:37:39,021 --> 00:37:40,939
Pie and pudding en flambe

861
00:37:40,939 --> 00:37:42,941
We'll prepare and serve
with flair

862
00:37:42,983 --> 00:37:45,026
A culinary cabaret

863
00:37:45,068 --> 00:37:47,153
You're alone and you're scared

864
00:37:47,195 --> 00:37:49,239
But the banquet's all prepared

865
00:37:49,280 --> 00:37:51,074
No one's gloomy or complaining

866
00:37:51,115 --> 00:37:53,117
While the flatware's
entertaining

867
00:37:53,201 --> 00:37:55,328
We tell jokes, l do tricks

868
00:37:55,369 --> 00:37:57,538
With my fellow candlesticks

869
00:37:57,580 --> 00:38:01,500
And it's all in perfect taste,
that you can bet

870
00:38:01,542 --> 00:38:03,585
Come on and lift your glass

871
00:38:03,627 --> 00:38:05,128
You've won your own free pass

872
00:38:05,170 --> 00:38:06,296
To be our guest--

873
00:38:06,338 --> 00:38:07,714
lf you're stressed

874
00:38:07,756 --> 00:38:09,799
lt's fine dining we suggest--

875
00:38:09,841 --> 00:38:12,135
Be our guest, be our guest

876
00:38:12,176 --> 00:38:13,886
Be our guest!

877
00:38:13,928 --> 00:38:17,098
Life is so unnerving

878
00:38:17,139 --> 00:38:20,059
For a servant who's not serving

879
00:38:20,100 --> 00:38:23,186
He's not whole
without a soul to wait upon

880
00:38:23,186 --> 00:38:24,855
Get off!

881
00:38:24,938 --> 00:38:28,274
Ah, those good old days
when we were useful

882
00:38:28,316 --> 00:38:29,818
Huh?

883
00:38:29,859 --> 00:38:31,778
Suddenly, those good
old days are gone

884
00:38:31,819 --> 00:38:34,530
Oh!

885
00:38:34,572 --> 00:38:36,324
Ten years we've been rusting

886
00:38:36,449 --> 00:38:38,659
Needing so much more
than dusting

887
00:38:38,701 --> 00:38:40,619
Needing exercise

888
00:38:40,703 --> 00:38:43,538
A chance to use our skills

889
00:38:43,580 --> 00:38:48,209
Most days we just
lay around the castle

890
00:38:48,209 --> 00:38:49,586
Flabby, fat and lazy

891
00:38:49,627 --> 00:38:51,671
You walked in and oops-a-daisy!

892
00:38:51,713 --> 00:38:53,506
lt's a guest, it's a guest!

893
00:38:53,506 --> 00:38:55,299
Sakes alive,
well, l'll be blessed

894
00:38:55,299 --> 00:38:57,259
Wine's been poured,
and thank the Lord

895
00:38:57,301 --> 00:38:59,136
l've had the napkins
freshly pressed

896
00:38:59,178 --> 00:39:01,430
With dessert, she'll want tea

897
00:39:01,472 --> 00:39:02,931
And, my dear,
that's fine with me

898
00:39:02,973 --> 00:39:05,016
While the cups
do their soft-shoeing

899
00:39:05,058 --> 00:39:07,018
l'll be bubbling,
l'll be brewing

900
00:39:07,060 --> 00:39:08,728
l'll get warm, piping hot

901
00:39:08,770 --> 00:39:10,772
Heaven's sake, is that a spot?

902
00:39:10,813 --> 00:39:13,441
Clean it up, we want
the company impressed

903
00:39:13,441 --> 00:39:15,484
We've got a lot to do

904
00:39:15,526 --> 00:39:17,278
ls it one lump or two?

905
00:39:17,319 --> 00:39:18,028
For you, our guest

906
00:39:18,070 --> 00:39:19,154
She's our guest

907
00:39:19,196 --> 00:39:20,364
She's our guest

908
00:39:20,406 --> 00:39:21,865
She's our guest

909
00:39:21,907 --> 00:39:25,786
People, fun's over,
over here, line up...

910
00:39:25,827 --> 00:39:27,662
lt's ten years since
we've had anybody here

911
00:39:27,704 --> 00:39:28,663
And we're obsessed

912
00:39:28,705 --> 00:39:30,832
With your meal, with your ease

913
00:39:30,874 --> 00:39:32,625
Yes, indeed, we aim to please

914
00:39:32,667 --> 00:39:34,961
While the candlelight's
still glowing

915
00:39:35,002 --> 00:39:39,006
Let us help you,
we'll keep going

916
00:39:39,048 --> 00:39:43,093
Course... by... course

917
00:39:43,135 --> 00:39:45,095
One by one

918
00:39:45,137 --> 00:39:47,681
Till you shout,
''Enough, l'm done!''

919
00:39:47,722 --> 00:39:51,893
Then we'll sing you
off to sleep as you digest

920
00:39:51,934 --> 00:39:53,978
Tonight you'll prop
your feet up

921
00:39:54,020 --> 00:39:55,563
But for now, let's eat up

922
00:39:55,563 --> 00:39:59,566
Be our guest, be our guest

923
00:39:59,608 --> 00:40:01,360
Be our guest

924
00:40:01,401 --> 00:40:09,409
Please be our guest!

925
00:40:11,619 --> 00:40:12,662
Bravo!

926
00:40:12,704 --> 00:40:13,996
That was wonderful.

927
00:40:13,996 --> 00:40:15,081
Thank you.

928
00:40:15,122 --> 00:40:17,208
Thank you, Mademoiselle.

929
00:40:17,249 --> 00:40:19,043
Good show, wasn't it?

930
00:40:19,084 --> 00:40:20,461
Yes, everyone.

931
00:40:20,461 --> 00:40:23,672
My goodness, look at the time.

932
00:40:23,714 --> 00:40:25,507
Now it's off to bed,
off to bed.

933
00:40:25,549 --> 00:40:27,968
Oh, l couldn't possibly
go to bed now.

934
00:40:28,009 --> 00:40:29,969
lt's my first time
in an enchanted castle.

935
00:40:30,011 --> 00:40:32,013
Enchanted!

936
00:40:32,055 --> 00:40:33,097
Who said anything

937
00:40:33,139 --> 00:40:34,891
about the castle
being enchanted?

938
00:40:34,932 --> 00:40:36,934
lt was you, wasn't it?

939
00:40:36,976 --> 00:40:38,686
l figured it out for myself.

940
00:40:41,396 --> 00:40:43,523
l'd like to look around,
if that's all right.

941
00:40:43,565 --> 00:40:45,067
Oh, would you like a tour?

942
00:40:45,108 --> 00:40:46,735
Wait a second, wait a second.

943
00:40:46,776 --> 00:40:48,486
l'm not sure that's
such a good idea.

944
00:40:48,528 --> 00:40:50,780
We can't let her
go poking around

945
00:40:50,780 --> 00:40:53,699
in certain places,
if you know what l mean.

946
00:40:53,699 --> 00:40:55,159
Perhaps you'd like to take me.

947
00:40:55,201 --> 00:40:56,577
l'm sure you know everything

948
00:40:56,619 --> 00:40:58,245
there is to know
about the castle.

949
00:40:58,287 --> 00:41:01,123
Oh, well, actually, l, uh...

950
00:41:01,165 --> 00:41:03,292
Yes, l do.

951
00:41:03,333 --> 00:41:04,418
As you can see

952
00:41:04,459 --> 00:41:07,254
the pseudo-facade
was stripped away

953
00:41:07,295 --> 00:41:09,464
to reveal a minimalist
rococo design.

954
00:41:09,506 --> 00:41:12,550
Note the unusual
inverted vaulted ceilings.

955
00:41:12,592 --> 00:41:13,926
This is yet another example

956
00:41:13,926 --> 00:41:15,886
of the late neoclassic
baroque period.

957
00:41:15,928 --> 00:41:17,221
and, as l always say

958
00:41:17,263 --> 00:41:19,348
if it's not baroque,
don't fix it.

959
00:41:21,183 --> 00:41:22,893
Uh, where was l?

960
00:41:24,061 --> 00:41:26,062
As you were.

961
00:41:26,104 --> 00:41:28,440
Now, then, if l may
draw your attention

962
00:41:28,481 --> 00:41:30,692
to the flying buttresses
above the...

963
00:41:30,733 --> 00:41:32,193
Uh, Mademoiselle?

964
00:41:37,698 --> 00:41:39,158
What's up there?

965
00:41:39,199 --> 00:41:40,117
Where? There?
Oh, nothing.

966
00:41:40,159 --> 00:41:41,493
Absolutely nothing
of interest at all

967
00:41:41,535 --> 00:41:42,744
in the west wing.

968
00:41:42,786 --> 00:41:44,746
Dusty, dull, very boring.

969
00:41:44,788 --> 00:41:47,249
Ah, so that's the west wing.

970
00:41:47,290 --> 00:41:48,958
Nice going.

971
00:41:49,000 --> 00:41:51,836
l wonder what
he's hiding up there?

972
00:41:51,878 --> 00:41:52,795
Hiding?

973
00:41:52,837 --> 00:41:54,255
The master is hiding nothing.

974
00:41:54,297 --> 00:41:56,007
Then it wouldn't be forbidden.

975
00:41:56,048 --> 00:41:58,384
Perhaps, uh,
Mademoiselle would like to

976
00:41:58,425 --> 00:42:00,052
uh-uh, uh... see something else.

977
00:42:00,052 --> 00:42:02,679
We have exquisite tapestries
dating all the way back to...

978
00:42:02,721 --> 00:42:03,639
maybe later.

979
00:42:03,680 --> 00:42:05,057
Th-The gardens or-or

980
00:42:05,057 --> 00:42:06,933
the-the-the-the library,
perhaps.

981
00:42:06,975 --> 00:42:08,143
You have a library?

982
00:42:08,184 --> 00:42:09,727
Yes, oh, indeed.

983
00:42:09,769 --> 00:42:10,812
With books.

984
00:42:10,853 --> 00:42:11,980
Scads of books!

985
00:42:12,021 --> 00:42:12,980
Mountains of books!

986
00:42:13,022 --> 00:42:13,981
Forests of books!

987
00:42:14,023 --> 00:42:14,982
-Cascades!
-Longboats!

988
00:42:15,066 --> 00:42:16,025
Swamps of books!

989
00:42:16,067 --> 00:42:17,860
More books than you'll

990
00:42:17,943 --> 00:42:19,903
ever be able
to read in a lifetime.

991
00:42:19,945 --> 00:42:22,364
Books on every subject ever
studied, by every author

992
00:42:22,447 --> 00:42:24,366
who ever set pen to paper.

993
00:43:14,162 --> 00:43:15,454
Oh!

994
00:43:59,328 --> 00:44:01,246
Why did you come here?

995
00:44:01,288 --> 00:44:03,165
l'm... l'm sorry.

996
00:44:03,206 --> 00:44:05,667
l warned you never to come here.

997
00:44:05,709 --> 00:44:06,835
l didn't mean any harm.

998
00:44:06,877 --> 00:44:09,504
Do you realize
what you could have done?!

999
00:44:10,004 --> 00:44:11,547
Please, stop.

1000
00:44:11,589 --> 00:44:13,299
Get out!

1001
00:44:13,341 --> 00:44:15,051
No!

1002
00:44:15,051 --> 00:44:18,846
Get... out!

1003
00:44:29,898 --> 00:44:30,982
Where are you going?

1004
00:44:31,024 --> 00:44:32,275
Promise or no promise

1005
00:44:32,316 --> 00:44:34,026
l can't stay here
another minute.

1006
00:44:34,026 --> 00:44:36,028
Oh, no, wait, please.

1007
00:44:36,112 --> 00:44:37,363
Please wait.

1008
00:45:15,147 --> 00:45:15,731
Oh!

1009
00:45:45,967 --> 00:45:46,593
Oh!

1010
00:46:56,907 --> 00:46:58,701
Here now.

1011
00:46:58,742 --> 00:47:00,160
Oh, don't do that.

1012
00:47:03,247 --> 00:47:05,999
Just hold still.

1013
00:47:07,292 --> 00:47:08,335
That hurts!

1014
00:47:08,376 --> 00:47:10,253
lf you'd hold still,
it wouldn't hurt as much!

1015
00:47:10,336 --> 00:47:11,629
Well, if you hadn't
have run away

1016
00:47:11,671 --> 00:47:12,839
this wouldn't have happened!

1017
00:47:12,880 --> 00:47:15,800
lf you hadn't frightened me,
l wouldn't have run away!

1018
00:47:15,841 --> 00:47:18,636
Well, you shouldn't have
been in the west wing!

1019
00:47:18,677 --> 00:47:20,804
Well, you should learn
to control your temper!

1020
00:47:22,806 --> 00:47:25,142
Now hold still.

1021
00:47:25,183 --> 00:47:26,977
This might sting a little.

1022
00:47:27,018 --> 00:47:28,061
Hmm?

1023
00:47:29,437 --> 00:47:32,565
By the way, thank you.

1024
00:47:32,607 --> 00:47:34,400
For saving my life.

1025
00:47:37,945 --> 00:47:40,489
You're welcome.

1026
00:47:47,120 --> 00:47:50,582
l don't usually leave the asylum
in the middle of the night

1027
00:47:50,623 --> 00:47:54,835
but he said you'd make it
worth my while.

1028
00:47:54,835 --> 00:47:56,253
Ah.

1029
00:47:56,337 --> 00:47:57,588
l'm listening.

1030
00:47:57,630 --> 00:47:59,006
lt's like this.

1031
00:47:59,006 --> 00:48:02,009
l've got my heart set
on marrying Belle

1032
00:48:02,050 --> 00:48:04,928
but she needs a little...
persuasion.

1033
00:48:05,011 --> 00:48:08,223
Turned him down flat.

1034
00:48:08,264 --> 00:48:09,891
Everyone knows
her father's a lunatic.

1035
00:48:09,933 --> 00:48:10,892
He was in here tonight

1036
00:48:10,934 --> 00:48:13,644
raving about a beast
in a castle.

1037
00:48:13,686 --> 00:48:15,313
Maurice is harmless.

1038
00:48:15,396 --> 00:48:17,898
The point is,
Belle would do anything

1039
00:48:17,940 --> 00:48:20,234
to keep him
from being locked up.

1040
00:48:22,027 --> 00:48:23,403
Yeah. Even marry him.

1041
00:48:26,072 --> 00:48:27,198
So you want me

1042
00:48:27,240 --> 00:48:29,200
to throw her father
into the asylum

1043
00:48:29,325 --> 00:48:32,036
unless she agrees to marry you.

1044
00:48:32,078 --> 00:48:35,498
Oh, that is despicable.

1045
00:48:35,539 --> 00:48:36,874
l love it!

1046
00:48:38,459 --> 00:48:40,627
lf no one will help me

1047
00:48:40,753 --> 00:48:42,337
then l'll go back alone.

1048
00:48:42,379 --> 00:48:43,964
Yes, is that everything?

1049
00:48:44,006 --> 00:48:45,882
l don't care what it takes.

1050
00:48:45,924 --> 00:48:48,176
l'll find that castle,
and somehow

1051
00:48:48,176 --> 00:48:50,011
l'll get her out of there.

1052
00:48:55,599 --> 00:48:57,143
Belle? Maurice?

1053
00:48:57,184 --> 00:48:59,061
Oh, well.

1054
00:48:59,061 --> 00:49:00,813
l guess it's not going
to work after all.

1055
00:49:00,854 --> 00:49:03,231
They have to come back sometime.

1056
00:49:03,273 --> 00:49:06,735
And when they do,
we'll be ready for them.

1057
00:49:06,776 --> 00:49:08,069
Lefou...

1058
00:49:08,111 --> 00:49:10,989
don't move from that spot

1059
00:49:11,030 --> 00:49:12,740
until Belle and
her father come home.

1060
00:49:12,740 --> 00:49:14,659
But, but, l...

1061
00:49:16,202 --> 00:49:18,078
Aw, nuts.

1062
00:49:39,890 --> 00:49:44,186
l've never felt this way
about anyone.

1063
00:49:44,227 --> 00:49:46,438
l want to do something for her.

1064
00:49:46,479 --> 00:49:48,023
But what?

1065
00:49:48,064 --> 00:49:50,024
Well, there's the usual things.

1066
00:49:50,066 --> 00:49:51,317
Flowers, chocolates.

1067
00:49:51,317 --> 00:49:53,069
Promises you don't intend
to keep.

1068
00:49:53,111 --> 00:49:54,820
Ah, no, no.

1069
00:49:54,862 --> 00:49:57,156
lt has to be something
very special.

1070
00:49:57,198 --> 00:49:59,325
Something that sparks
her interest.

1071
00:49:59,366 --> 00:50:00,576
Wait a minute!

1072
00:50:03,287 --> 00:50:07,123
Belle, there's something
l want to show you.

1073
00:50:07,165 --> 00:50:11,044
But first, you have
to close your eyes.

1074
00:50:13,004 --> 00:50:14,505
lt's a surprise.

1075
00:50:25,182 --> 00:50:26,600
Can l open them?

1076
00:50:26,641 --> 00:50:28,560
No, no. Not yet.

1077
00:50:28,601 --> 00:50:31,187
Wait here.

1078
00:50:35,191 --> 00:50:36,567
Now can l open them?

1079
00:50:36,609 --> 00:50:38,194
All right.

1080
00:50:38,235 --> 00:50:39,320
Now.

1081
00:50:47,702 --> 00:50:49,996
l can't believe it!

1082
00:50:50,038 --> 00:50:52,165
l've never seen so many books
in all my life!

1083
00:50:52,206 --> 00:50:53,791
You-You like it?

1084
00:50:53,833 --> 00:50:55,418
lt's wonderful!

1085
00:50:55,459 --> 00:50:57,336
Then it's yours.

1086
00:50:57,336 --> 00:50:59,255
Oh, thank you so much.

1087
00:50:59,296 --> 00:51:00,923
Oh, would you look at that!

1088
00:51:00,964 --> 00:51:02,799
l knew it would work.

1089
00:51:02,841 --> 00:51:03,967
What? What worked?

1090
00:51:04,009 --> 00:51:06,636
lt's very encouraging.

1091
00:51:06,678 --> 00:51:08,263
lsn't this exciting?

1092
00:51:08,388 --> 00:51:09,639
l didn't see anything.

1093
00:51:09,681 --> 00:51:10,807
Come along, Chip.

1094
00:51:10,848 --> 00:51:12,517
There's chores to be done
in the kitchen.

1095
00:51:12,558 --> 00:51:13,935
But what are they talking about?

1096
00:51:13,976 --> 00:51:15,269
What's going on?
Come on, Mom.

1097
00:52:00,728 --> 00:52:02,729
There's something sweet

1098
00:52:02,771 --> 00:52:04,356
And almost kind

1099
00:52:04,398 --> 00:52:07,859
But he was mean,
and he was coarse and unrefined

1100
00:52:07,901 --> 00:52:11,738
And now he's dear, and so unsure

1101
00:52:11,779 --> 00:52:14,282
l wonder why l didn't see it
there before

1102
00:52:28,211 --> 00:52:30,421
She glanced this way

1103
00:52:30,463 --> 00:52:31,923
l thought l saw

1104
00:52:31,964 --> 00:52:35,551
And when we touched,
she didn't shudder at my paw

1105
00:52:35,593 --> 00:52:37,178
No, it can't be

1106
00:52:37,219 --> 00:52:39,221
l'll just ignore

1107
00:52:39,263 --> 00:52:43,100
But then she's never looked
at me that way before

1108
00:52:45,560 --> 00:52:51,357
New and a bit alarming

1109
00:52:51,399 --> 00:52:59,531
Who'd have ever thought
that this could be?

1110
00:52:59,573 --> 00:53:06,079
True that he's no
Prince Charming

1111
00:53:06,121 --> 00:53:08,581
But there's something in him

1112
00:53:08,623 --> 00:53:13,878
That l simply didn't see...

1113
00:53:13,920 --> 00:53:15,046
Well, who'd have thought?

1114
00:53:15,087 --> 00:53:16,005
Well, bless my soul

1115
00:53:16,047 --> 00:53:17,131
Well, who'd have known?

1116
00:53:17,173 --> 00:53:18,048
Well, who indeed?

1117
00:53:18,090 --> 00:53:19,049
And who'd have guessed

1118
00:53:19,091 --> 00:53:20,509
They'd come together
on their own?

1119
00:53:20,551 --> 00:53:21,468
lt's so peculiar

1120
00:53:21,468 --> 00:53:22,427
We'll wait and see

1121
00:53:22,469 --> 00:53:25,180
A few days more

1122
00:53:25,222 --> 00:53:29,434
There may be something there
that wasn't there before...

1123
00:53:29,476 --> 00:53:31,227
You know, perhaps there is

1124
00:53:31,269 --> 00:53:34,272
Something there
that wasn't there before

1125
00:53:34,313 --> 00:53:36,023
What?

1126
00:53:36,023 --> 00:53:39,318
There may be something there
that wasn't there before.

1127
00:53:39,401 --> 00:53:40,903
What's there, Mama?

1128
00:53:40,944 --> 00:53:42,237
Shh!

1129
00:53:42,279 --> 00:53:46,199
l'll tell you when you're older.

1130
00:53:46,241 --> 00:53:47,158
Right, then!

1131
00:53:47,200 --> 00:53:48,743
You all know why we're here.

1132
00:53:48,785 --> 00:53:52,163
We have exactly 12 hours,
36 minutes and 15 seconds

1133
00:53:52,205 --> 00:53:53,956
to create the most magical

1134
00:53:53,998 --> 00:53:57,877
spontaneous, romantic atmosphere
known to man or beast.

1135
00:53:57,918 --> 00:53:59,211
''Or beast...''

1136
00:54:01,797 --> 00:54:03,507
Right.

1137
00:54:03,507 --> 00:54:04,925
Need l remind you

1138
00:54:04,925 --> 00:54:08,386
that if the last petal falls
from this rose

1139
00:54:08,428 --> 00:54:09,637
the spell will never be...

1140
00:54:09,679 --> 00:54:11,472
broken!

1141
00:54:11,514 --> 00:54:12,932
Very well.

1142
00:54:12,974 --> 00:54:14,892
You all know your assignments.

1143
00:54:14,934 --> 00:54:16,769
Half of you to the west wing.

1144
00:54:16,811 --> 00:54:18,562
Half of you to the east wing.

1145
00:54:18,604 --> 00:54:20,564
The rest of you, come with me.

1146
00:54:24,985 --> 00:54:28,279
Oh, lighten up, Cogsworth,
and let nature take its course.

1147
00:54:28,321 --> 00:54:30,865
lt's obvious there's
a spark between them.

1148
00:54:30,907 --> 00:54:33,701
Yes, but there's no harm
in fanning the flames.

1149
00:54:33,743 --> 00:54:35,494
You know... a little.

1150
00:54:36,454 --> 00:54:37,663
Besides, they must fall in love

1151
00:54:37,705 --> 00:54:39,415
tonight if we ever expect
to be human again.

1152
00:54:39,456 --> 00:54:40,791
Ah, human again.

1153
00:54:40,833 --> 00:54:42,292
Human again.

1154
00:54:42,376 --> 00:54:45,295
Yes, think what that means.

1155
00:54:48,048 --> 00:54:50,508
l'll be cooking again

1156
00:54:50,550 --> 00:54:52,385
Be good looking again

1157
00:54:52,427 --> 00:54:56,013
With a mademoiselle on each arm

1158
00:54:56,055 --> 00:54:58,599
When l'm human again

1159
00:54:58,641 --> 00:55:00,225
Only human again

1160
00:55:00,267 --> 00:55:03,687
Poised and polished
and gleaming with charm

1161
00:55:03,729 --> 00:55:05,480
l'll be courting again

1162
00:55:05,480 --> 00:55:07,274
Chic and sporting again

1163
00:55:07,315 --> 00:55:10,151
Which should cause
several husbands alarm

1164
00:55:10,151 --> 00:55:12,695
Ha, ha!
l'll hop down off this shelf

1165
00:55:12,737 --> 00:55:14,530
And tout de suite be myself

1166
00:55:14,572 --> 00:55:17,491
l can't wait to be human again

1167
00:55:19,410 --> 00:55:21,495
When we're human again

1168
00:55:21,537 --> 00:55:23,288
Only human again

1169
00:55:23,330 --> 00:55:26,082
When we're knickknacks
and whatnots no more

1170
00:55:26,124 --> 00:55:30,753
When we're human again,
good and human again

1171
00:55:30,795 --> 00:55:33,172
Oh, cherie,
won't it all be top drawer?

1172
00:55:33,214 --> 00:55:35,132
l'll wear lipstick and rouge

1173
00:55:35,174 --> 00:55:36,425
And l won't be so huge

1174
00:55:36,467 --> 00:55:39,970
Why, l'll easily fit
through that door

1175
00:55:40,012 --> 00:55:41,805
l'll exude savoir faire

1176
00:55:41,805 --> 00:55:43,724
l'll wear gowns, l'll have hair

1177
00:55:43,724 --> 00:55:46,768
lt's my prayer to be human again

1178
00:55:51,773 --> 00:55:53,232
When we're human again

1179
00:55:53,316 --> 00:55:54,942
Only human again

1180
00:55:54,984 --> 00:55:58,195
When the world once more
starts making sense

1181
00:55:58,237 --> 00:55:59,822
l'll unwind, for a change

1182
00:55:59,822 --> 00:56:01,490
Really? That'd be strange

1183
00:56:01,532 --> 00:56:04,493
Can l help it if l'm t-t-tense?

1184
00:56:04,534 --> 00:56:05,911
ln a shack by the sea

1185
00:56:05,952 --> 00:56:07,662
l'll sit back, sipping tea

1186
00:56:07,662 --> 00:56:10,873
Let my early retirement commence

1187
00:56:10,915 --> 00:56:12,542
Far from fools made of wax

1188
00:56:12,583 --> 00:56:16,170
l'll get down to brass tacks
and relax!

1189
00:56:16,170 --> 00:56:19,757
When l'm human again

1190
00:56:19,798 --> 00:56:23,176
So sweep the dust from the floor

1191
00:56:23,218 --> 00:56:26,596
Let's let some light in the room

1192
00:56:26,638 --> 00:56:28,223
l can feel, l can tell

1193
00:56:28,223 --> 00:56:31,184
Someone might break the spell
any day now

1194
00:56:32,852 --> 00:56:36,105
Shine up the brass on the door

1195
00:56:36,147 --> 00:56:38,899
Alert the dust pail and broom

1196
00:56:38,941 --> 00:56:40,901
lf it all goes as planned

1197
00:56:40,901 --> 00:56:46,031
Our time may be at hand
any day now

1198
00:56:46,031 --> 00:56:49,284
Open the shutters,
and let in some air

1199
00:56:49,325 --> 00:56:53,121
Put these here,
and put those over there

1200
00:56:53,162 --> 00:56:56,457
Sweep up the years
of sadness and tears

1201
00:56:56,499 --> 00:56:59,084
And throw them away

1202
00:57:04,965 --> 00:57:07,550
We'll be human again

1203
00:57:07,592 --> 00:57:09,677
Only human again

1204
00:57:09,719 --> 00:57:12,305
When the girl
finally sets us all free

1205
00:57:12,347 --> 00:57:14,807
Cheeks a-blooming again

1206
00:57:14,849 --> 00:57:16,600
We're assuming again

1207
00:57:16,684 --> 00:57:19,478
We'll resume our
long lost joie de vivre

1208
00:57:19,520 --> 00:57:20,687
We'll be playing again

1209
00:57:20,729 --> 00:57:22,898
Holidaying again

1210
00:57:22,940 --> 00:57:25,984
And we're praying it's ASAP

1211
00:57:26,026 --> 00:57:27,986
We will push, we will shove

1212
00:57:28,028 --> 00:57:29,863
They will both fall in love

1213
00:57:29,863 --> 00:57:33,574
And we'll finally
be human again...

1214
00:57:35,117 --> 00:57:38,162
For never was a story
of more woe

1215
00:57:38,204 --> 00:57:41,373
Than this of Juliet
and her Romeo.

1216
00:57:41,415 --> 00:57:43,792
Could you read it again?

1217
00:57:43,834 --> 00:57:45,919
Well, here, why don't
you read it to me?

1218
00:57:45,961 --> 00:57:48,046
Uh, all right.

1219
00:57:48,088 --> 00:57:50,798
Uh...

1220
00:57:50,840 --> 00:57:53,050
Uh... l can't.

1221
00:57:53,092 --> 00:57:55,720
You mean, you never learned?

1222
00:57:55,761 --> 00:57:57,847
l learned... a little.

1223
00:57:57,930 --> 00:58:00,432
lt's just been so long.

1224
00:58:00,474 --> 00:58:02,643
Well, here, l'll help you.

1225
00:58:02,726 --> 00:58:04,227
Let's start here.

1226
00:58:04,269 --> 00:58:06,897
Here.

1227
00:58:06,897 --> 00:58:08,815
Okay, ''Twoe...''

1228
00:58:08,857 --> 00:58:09,774
''Two.''

1229
00:58:09,816 --> 00:58:11,818
''Two... l knew that.

1230
00:58:11,859 --> 00:58:14,445
Two households...''

1231
00:58:14,487 --> 00:58:18,365
We'll be dancing again

1232
00:58:18,449 --> 00:58:19,992
We'll be twirling again

1233
00:58:20,034 --> 00:58:23,453
We'll be whirling around
with such ease

1234
00:58:23,495 --> 00:58:24,704
When we're human again

1235
00:58:24,830 --> 00:58:26,414
Only human again

1236
00:58:26,456 --> 00:58:29,959
We'll go waltzing
those old one, two, threes

1237
00:58:30,001 --> 00:58:31,836
We'll be floating again

1238
00:58:31,878 --> 00:58:33,087
We'll be gliding again

1239
00:58:33,129 --> 00:58:36,632
Stepping, striding
as fine as you please

1240
00:58:36,674 --> 00:58:39,885
Like a real human does

1241
00:58:39,927 --> 00:58:43,221
l'll be all that l was

1242
00:58:43,305 --> 00:58:47,642
On that glorious morn
when we're finally reborn

1243
00:58:47,684 --> 00:58:51,104
And we're all

1244
00:58:51,145 --> 00:58:56,150
Human again!

1245
00:59:08,411 --> 00:59:11,247
Tonight is the night.

1246
00:59:11,289 --> 00:59:13,916
l'm not sure l can do this.

1247
00:59:13,958 --> 00:59:15,459
You don't have time to be timid.

1248
00:59:15,501 --> 00:59:17,670
You must be bold, daring.

1249
00:59:17,711 --> 00:59:19,380
Bold, daring.

1250
00:59:22,216 --> 00:59:24,301
There will be music...

1251
00:59:24,342 --> 00:59:26,678
romantic candlelight...

1252
00:59:26,678 --> 00:59:28,596
provided by myself.

1253
00:59:28,596 --> 00:59:30,014
And when the moment is right

1254
00:59:30,056 --> 00:59:31,808
you confess your love.

1255
00:59:31,849 --> 00:59:33,726
Yes, l con...

1256
00:59:33,768 --> 00:59:36,479
l-l... No, l can't.

1257
00:59:36,520 --> 00:59:37,897
You care for the girl,
don't you?

1258
00:59:37,897 --> 00:59:40,107
More than anything.

1259
00:59:40,149 --> 00:59:41,775
Well, then,
you must tell her.

1260
00:59:43,777 --> 00:59:45,070
Voila!

1261
00:59:45,112 --> 00:59:47,364
Oh, you look so... so...

1262
00:59:47,405 --> 00:59:49,240
Stupid.

1263
00:59:49,282 --> 00:59:52,285
Not quite the word
l was looking for.

1264
00:59:52,326 --> 00:59:54,287
Perhaps a little more
off the top?

1265
00:59:56,580 --> 01:00:01,585
Your lady awaits.

1266
01:00:23,438 --> 01:00:28,485
Tale as old as time

1267
01:00:28,526 --> 01:00:30,820
True as it can be

1268
01:00:33,531 --> 01:00:36,242
Barely even friends

1269
01:00:36,283 --> 01:00:38,744
Then somebody bends

1270
01:00:38,786 --> 01:00:40,913
Unexpectedly

1271
01:00:42,539 --> 01:00:45,167
Just a little change

1272
01:00:48,128 --> 01:00:50,672
Small, to say the least

1273
01:00:50,713 --> 01:00:53,174
Both a little scared

1274
01:00:53,216 --> 01:00:56,177
Neither one prepared

1275
01:00:56,302 --> 01:00:58,929
Beauty and the Beast

1276
01:01:01,765 --> 01:01:03,558
Ever just the same

1277
01:01:06,561 --> 01:01:09,022
Ever a surprise

1278
01:01:09,063 --> 01:01:11,107
Huh? Huh? Huh?

1279
01:01:11,149 --> 01:01:13,776
Ever as before

1280
01:01:13,818 --> 01:01:16,112
Ever just as sure

1281
01:01:16,153 --> 01:01:19,531
As the sun will rise

1282
01:01:20,991 --> 01:01:25,537
Tale as old as time

1283
01:01:25,579 --> 01:01:29,958
Tune as old as song

1284
01:01:29,999 --> 01:01:33,086
Bittersweet and strange

1285
01:01:33,127 --> 01:01:35,463
Finding you can change

1286
01:01:35,546 --> 01:01:38,340
Learning you were wrong

1287
01:01:40,217 --> 01:01:44,763
Certain as the sun

1288
01:01:44,805 --> 01:01:47,557
Rising in the east

1289
01:01:47,599 --> 01:01:49,767
Tale as old as time

1290
01:01:49,767 --> 01:01:52,437
Song as old as rhyme

1291
01:01:52,478 --> 01:01:55,398
Beauty and the Beast

1292
01:01:55,439 --> 01:01:57,108
Shh!

1293
01:01:58,192 --> 01:02:01,653
Tale as old as time

1294
01:02:01,695 --> 01:02:05,699
Song as old as rhyme

1295
01:02:05,740 --> 01:02:12,580
Beauty and the Beast.

1296
01:02:12,622 --> 01:02:16,125
Off to the cupboard
with you now, Chip.

1297
01:02:16,167 --> 01:02:18,252
lt's past your bedtime.

1298
01:02:18,294 --> 01:02:20,629
Good night, love.

1299
01:02:43,108 --> 01:02:46,486
Belle?

1300
01:02:46,528 --> 01:02:49,864
Are you... happy here with me?

1301
01:02:49,906 --> 01:02:51,616
Yes.

1302
01:02:55,494 --> 01:02:57,913
What is it?

1303
01:02:57,913 --> 01:03:00,499
lf only l could see
my father again

1304
01:03:00,541 --> 01:03:02,125
just for a moment.

1305
01:03:02,125 --> 01:03:03,502
l miss him so much.

1306
01:03:08,965 --> 01:03:11,759
There is a way.

1307
01:03:12,927 --> 01:03:15,388
This mirror will show
you anything...

1308
01:03:15,429 --> 01:03:18,724
anything you wish to see.

1309
01:03:18,724 --> 01:03:21,477
l'd like to see my father,
please.

1310
01:03:28,149 --> 01:03:29,275
Papa?

1311
01:03:29,317 --> 01:03:30,485
Oh, no.

1312
01:03:30,526 --> 01:03:32,653
He's sick.

1313
01:03:32,695 --> 01:03:36,198
He may be dying
and he's all alone.

1314
01:03:41,203 --> 01:03:44,539
Then, you must go to him.

1315
01:03:44,581 --> 01:03:45,832
What did you say?

1316
01:03:45,874 --> 01:03:46,875
l release you.

1317
01:03:46,958 --> 01:03:49,252
You are no longer my prisoner.

1318
01:03:49,294 --> 01:03:51,838
You mean... l'm free?

1319
01:03:51,879 --> 01:03:53,840
Yes.

1320
01:03:53,881 --> 01:03:55,966
Oh, thank you.

1321
01:03:56,008 --> 01:03:58,093
Hold on, Papa.

1322
01:03:58,135 --> 01:04:00,304
l'm on my way.

1323
01:04:00,345 --> 01:04:02,055
Take it with you

1324
01:04:02,097 --> 01:04:06,351
so you'll always have
a way to look back

1325
01:04:06,393 --> 01:04:08,144
and remember me.

1326
01:04:10,688 --> 01:04:13,524
Thank you for understanding
how much he needs me.

1327
01:04:21,782 --> 01:04:24,159
Well, Your Highness, l must say

1328
01:04:24,201 --> 01:04:26,828
everything is going
just swimmingly.

1329
01:04:26,870 --> 01:04:28,830
l knew you had it in you.

1330
01:04:28,872 --> 01:04:30,290
l let her go.

1331
01:04:30,290 --> 01:04:32,208
Yes, yes.

1332
01:04:32,208 --> 01:04:34,001
Splen...

1333
01:04:34,001 --> 01:04:36,754
You what?

1334
01:04:36,879 --> 01:04:38,297
How could you do that?

1335
01:04:38,339 --> 01:04:39,757
l had to.

1336
01:04:39,798 --> 01:04:41,341
Yes, but...

1337
01:04:41,383 --> 01:04:42,634
Why?

1338
01:04:42,676 --> 01:04:46,179
Because... l love her.

1339
01:04:46,221 --> 01:04:47,681
He did what?

1340
01:04:47,722 --> 01:04:48,848
Yes.

1341
01:04:48,890 --> 01:04:50,558
l'm afraid it's true.

1342
01:04:50,600 --> 01:04:51,934
She's going away?

1343
01:04:51,976 --> 01:04:53,936
But he was so close.

1344
01:04:53,978 --> 01:04:58,232
After all this time,
he's finally learned to love.

1345
01:04:58,274 --> 01:05:00,859
That's it, then.
That should break the spell.

1346
01:05:00,901 --> 01:05:02,361
But it's not enough.

1347
01:05:02,402 --> 01:05:04,696
She has to love him in return.

1348
01:05:04,738 --> 01:05:07,907
Now it's too late.

1349
01:05:16,082 --> 01:05:18,834
Papa! Papa!

1350
01:05:31,179 --> 01:05:33,306
Ooh.

1351
01:05:33,347 --> 01:05:35,391
They're back.

1352
01:05:36,559 --> 01:05:37,768
Belle?

1353
01:05:37,810 --> 01:05:38,769
Shh.

1354
01:05:38,811 --> 01:05:40,187
lt's all right, Papa.

1355
01:05:40,187 --> 01:05:42,231
l'm home.

1356
01:05:42,272 --> 01:05:43,398
l thought l'd never

1357
01:05:43,398 --> 01:05:45,901
see you again.

1358
01:05:45,942 --> 01:05:47,694
l missed you so much.

1359
01:05:47,777 --> 01:05:48,695
But the Beast?

1360
01:05:48,737 --> 01:05:50,613
Did you... how did you escape?

1361
01:05:50,613 --> 01:05:51,906
l didn't escape, Papa.

1362
01:05:51,906 --> 01:05:53,116
He let me go.

1363
01:05:53,157 --> 01:05:54,450
That horrible beast?

1364
01:05:54,533 --> 01:05:57,453
But he's different now, Papa.

1365
01:05:57,495 --> 01:05:59,663
He's changed somehow.

1366
01:06:03,542 --> 01:06:04,751
Hi.

1367
01:06:04,793 --> 01:06:07,545
Oh. A stowaway.

1368
01:06:07,587 --> 01:06:10,882
Why, hello there, little fella.

1369
01:06:10,924 --> 01:06:12,675
Didn't think l'd see you again.

1370
01:06:12,717 --> 01:06:14,135
Belle, why'd you go away?

1371
01:06:14,176 --> 01:06:15,720
Don't you like us anymore?

1372
01:06:15,761 --> 01:06:18,681
Oh, Chip, of course l do.

1373
01:06:18,722 --> 01:06:20,682
lt's just...

1374
01:06:23,518 --> 01:06:24,644
May l help you?

1375
01:06:24,686 --> 01:06:26,563
l've come to collect
your father.

1376
01:06:26,605 --> 01:06:28,023
My father?

1377
01:06:28,064 --> 01:06:29,983
Don't worry, Mademoiselle.

1378
01:06:29,983 --> 01:06:32,110
We'll take good care of him.

1379
01:06:33,402 --> 01:06:34,528
My father's not crazy.

1380
01:06:34,570 --> 01:06:36,280
He was raving like a lunatic.

1381
01:06:36,322 --> 01:06:38,115
We all heard him, didn't we?

1382
01:06:40,951 --> 01:06:42,452
No, l won't let you.

1383
01:06:42,536 --> 01:06:43,412
Belle?

1384
01:06:43,453 --> 01:06:45,997
Maurice, tell us again, old man.

1385
01:06:46,039 --> 01:06:47,916
Just how big was the beast?

1386
01:06:49,626 --> 01:06:53,004
He was... l mean, he was...
he was... enormous.

1387
01:06:53,129 --> 01:06:54,755
l-l'd say at least eight...

1388
01:06:54,797 --> 01:06:57,091
No, more like ten feet.

1389
01:06:57,133 --> 01:07:01,053
Well, you don't get
much crazier than that.

1390
01:07:02,262 --> 01:07:04,347
lt's true, l tell you.

1391
01:07:04,389 --> 01:07:06,266
Get him out of here.

1392
01:07:06,308 --> 01:07:07,517
Let go of me.

1393
01:07:07,559 --> 01:07:08,643
No!

1394
01:07:08,685 --> 01:07:10,645
You can't do this.

1395
01:07:10,687 --> 01:07:11,521
Poor Belle.

1396
01:07:11,562 --> 01:07:14,065
lt's a shame about your father.

1397
01:07:14,106 --> 01:07:15,900
You know he's not crazy, Gaston.

1398
01:07:15,941 --> 01:07:18,736
Hmm, l might be able
to clear up this...

1399
01:07:18,777 --> 01:07:20,404
little misunderstanding.

1400
01:07:20,446 --> 01:07:21,488
lf...

1401
01:07:21,530 --> 01:07:22,322
lf what?

1402
01:07:22,364 --> 01:07:24,241
lf you marry me.

1403
01:07:24,282 --> 01:07:25,200
What?

1404
01:07:25,242 --> 01:07:26,826
One little word, Belle.
That's all it takes.

1405
01:07:26,868 --> 01:07:27,827
Never.

1406
01:07:27,869 --> 01:07:29,412
Have it your way.

1407
01:07:29,496 --> 01:07:30,246
Belle.

1408
01:07:31,873 --> 01:07:33,374
Let go of me.

1409
01:07:33,416 --> 01:07:35,918
My father's not crazy
and l can prove it.

1410
01:07:35,960 --> 01:07:38,087
Show me the Beast.

1411
01:07:42,549 --> 01:07:43,800
ls it dangerous?

1412
01:07:43,842 --> 01:07:46,177
Oh, no, no,
he'd never hurt anyone.

1413
01:07:46,219 --> 01:07:50,515
Please, l know he looks vicious,
but he's really kind and gentle.

1414
01:07:50,598 --> 01:07:52,100
He's my friend.

1415
01:07:52,141 --> 01:07:53,309
lf l didn't know better

1416
01:07:53,351 --> 01:07:55,770
l'd think you had feelings
for this monster.

1417
01:07:55,811 --> 01:07:58,272
He's no monster, Gaston.
You are.

1418
01:07:59,398 --> 01:08:02,234
She's as crazy as the old man.

1419
01:08:03,777 --> 01:08:05,529
The Beast will make off
with your children.

1420
01:08:05,570 --> 01:08:06,404
-He'll come after them
in the night.
-No!

1421
01:08:06,446 --> 01:08:07,364
We're not safe

1422
01:08:07,405 --> 01:08:08,907
till his head
is mounted on my wall.

1423
01:08:08,948 --> 01:08:10,658
l say we kill the Beast!

1424
01:08:11,659 --> 01:08:13,369
We're not safe until he's dead

1425
01:08:13,411 --> 01:08:14,912
He'll come stalking us at night

1426
01:08:14,954 --> 01:08:16,831
Set to sacrifice our children

1427
01:08:16,831 --> 01:08:18,540
To his monstrous appetite

1428
01:08:18,582 --> 01:08:20,250
He'll wreak havoc on our village

1429
01:08:20,376 --> 01:08:21,793
lf we let him wander free

1430
01:08:21,835 --> 01:08:25,380
So it's time to take
some action, boys

1431
01:08:25,422 --> 01:08:30,343
lt's time to follow me

1432
01:08:31,969 --> 01:08:33,763
Through the mist,
through the woods

1433
01:08:33,804 --> 01:08:35,556
Through the darkness
and the shadows

1434
01:08:35,598 --> 01:08:37,892
lt's a nightmare,
but it's one exciting ride

1435
01:08:37,933 --> 01:08:41,228
Say a prayer, then we're there
at the drawbridge of a castle

1436
01:08:41,270 --> 01:08:44,564
And there's something
truly terrible inside

1437
01:08:44,606 --> 01:08:47,150
lt's a beast, he's got fangs,
razor-sharp ones

1438
01:08:47,192 --> 01:08:50,403
Massive paws, killer claws
for the feast

1439
01:08:50,445 --> 01:08:52,321
Hear him roar, see him foam

1440
01:08:52,363 --> 01:08:54,031
But we're not coming home

1441
01:08:54,031 --> 01:08:55,366
Till he's dead

1442
01:08:55,408 --> 01:08:57,076
Good and dead

1443
01:08:57,118 --> 01:08:58,160
Kill the Beast!

1444
01:08:58,202 --> 01:08:59,745
No, l won't let you do this.

1445
01:08:59,787 --> 01:09:02,206
lf you're not with us,
you're against us.

1446
01:09:02,247 --> 01:09:03,248
Bring the old man.

1447
01:09:03,290 --> 01:09:04,833
Get your hands off me.

1448
01:09:04,875 --> 01:09:07,210
We can't have them running off
to warn the creature.

1449
01:09:07,252 --> 01:09:08,461
Let us out!

1450
01:09:08,503 --> 01:09:11,047
We'll rid the village
of this beast.

1451
01:09:11,089 --> 01:09:12,173
Who's with me?

1452
01:09:13,633 --> 01:09:15,593
Raise your torch,
mount your horse

1453
01:09:15,634 --> 01:09:17,887
Screw your courage
to the sticking place

1454
01:09:17,928 --> 01:09:20,264
We're counting on Gaston
to lead the way

1455
01:09:20,305 --> 01:09:22,015
Through the mist,
through the wood

1456
01:09:22,057 --> 01:09:23,600
Where, within a haunted castle

1457
01:09:23,642 --> 01:09:26,186
Something's lurking
that you don't see every day

1458
01:09:26,228 --> 01:09:29,647
lt's a beast,
one as tall as a mountain

1459
01:09:29,689 --> 01:09:32,734
We won't rest
till he's good and deceased

1460
01:09:32,775 --> 01:09:34,485
Sally forth, tally ho

1461
01:09:34,527 --> 01:09:36,028
Grab your sword, grab your bow

1462
01:09:36,112 --> 01:09:37,571
Praise the Lord, and here we go.

1463
01:09:37,613 --> 01:09:40,824
We'll lay siege to the castle
and bring back his head!

1464
01:09:40,949 --> 01:09:43,076
l have to warn the Beast.

1465
01:09:43,118 --> 01:09:44,953
This is all my fault.

1466
01:09:44,995 --> 01:09:46,788
Oh, Papa, what are
we going to do?

1467
01:09:46,830 --> 01:09:48,123
Now, now.

1468
01:09:48,164 --> 01:09:49,624
We'll think of something.

1469
01:09:52,585 --> 01:09:53,711
Ah!

1470
01:09:56,547 --> 01:09:58,841
We don't like
what we don't understand

1471
01:09:58,882 --> 01:10:00,551
ln fact, it scares us

1472
01:10:00,551 --> 01:10:03,095
And this monster
is mysterious at least

1473
01:10:03,136 --> 01:10:04,513
Bring your guns,
bring your knives

1474
01:10:04,596 --> 01:10:06,056
Save your children
and your wives

1475
01:10:06,097 --> 01:10:09,058
We'll save our village
and our lives

1476
01:10:09,100 --> 01:10:10,518
We'll kill the Beast!

1477
01:10:10,560 --> 01:10:11,894
l knew it.

1478
01:10:11,936 --> 01:10:14,230
l knew it was foolish
to get our hopes up.

1479
01:10:14,230 --> 01:10:16,982
Maybe it would have been better
if she'd never come at all.

1480
01:10:18,150 --> 01:10:19,360
Could it be?

1481
01:10:19,401 --> 01:10:20,110
ls it she?

1482
01:10:20,194 --> 01:10:21,528
Sacre bleu!

1483
01:10:21,570 --> 01:10:22,487
lnvaders.

1484
01:10:22,529 --> 01:10:23,780
Encroachers.

1485
01:10:23,822 --> 01:10:25,115
And they have the mirror.

1486
01:10:25,157 --> 01:10:26,116
Warn the master.

1487
01:10:26,157 --> 01:10:28,034
lf it's a fight they want,
we'll be ready for them.

1488
01:10:28,076 --> 01:10:28,952
Who's with me?

1489
01:10:28,993 --> 01:10:29,953
Ah!

1490
01:10:29,994 --> 01:10:31,913
Take whatever booty you can find

1491
01:10:31,954 --> 01:10:34,916
but remember, the Beast is mine!

1492
01:10:34,957 --> 01:10:36,625
Lights ablaze, banners high

1493
01:10:36,667 --> 01:10:38,294
We go marching into battle

1494
01:10:38,335 --> 01:10:40,921
Unafraid, although
the danger just increased

1495
01:10:40,963 --> 01:10:42,631
Raise the flag, sing the song

1496
01:10:42,673 --> 01:10:43,924
Here we come, we're 50 strong

1497
01:10:43,965 --> 01:10:46,426
And 50 Frenchmen can't be wrong

1498
01:10:46,426 --> 01:10:48,178
Let's kill the Beast!

1499
01:10:50,763 --> 01:10:52,181
-Pardon me, Master?
-Leave me in peace.

1500
01:10:52,181 --> 01:10:54,475
But, sir, the castle
is under attack.

1501
01:10:54,517 --> 01:10:57,478
Kill the Beast!
Kill the Beast!

1502
01:10:57,561 --> 01:10:59,271
This isn't working.

1503
01:10:59,313 --> 01:11:01,690
Oh, Lumiere,
we must do something.

1504
01:11:01,732 --> 01:11:04,109
Wait, l know.

1505
01:11:06,403 --> 01:11:09,114
What shall we do, Master?

1506
01:11:09,155 --> 01:11:11,532
lt doesn't matter now.

1507
01:11:11,574 --> 01:11:13,576
Just let them come.

1508
01:11:13,618 --> 01:11:16,787
Kill the Beast!
Kill the Beast!

1509
01:11:16,829 --> 01:11:17,997
Kill the Beast!

1510
01:11:30,508 --> 01:11:31,175
Now!

1511
01:11:51,319 --> 01:11:52,528
Yes!

1512
01:11:55,948 --> 01:11:57,575
Here we go.

1513
01:12:00,744 --> 01:12:02,287
What the devil?

1514
01:12:03,372 --> 01:12:04,581
Belle, look out!

1515
01:12:10,545 --> 01:12:13,714
You guys got to try this thing.

1516
01:12:18,010 --> 01:12:22,222
Up here you scurvy scum! Now!

1517
01:12:39,613 --> 01:12:40,864
Oh!

1518
01:13:29,159 --> 01:13:31,536
And stay out!

1519
01:13:33,329 --> 01:13:34,997
Eww!

1520
01:13:59,770 --> 01:14:01,021
Get up.

1521
01:14:02,356 --> 01:14:04,900
Get up!

1522
01:14:04,941 --> 01:14:07,527
What's the matter, Beast?

1523
01:14:07,569 --> 01:14:10,989
Too kind and gentle
to fight back?

1524
01:14:17,453 --> 01:14:18,787
No!

1525
01:14:22,291 --> 01:14:23,000
Belle...

1526
01:14:23,041 --> 01:14:25,377
No! Gaston, don't!

1527
01:14:30,798 --> 01:14:33,593
Let's go, Philippe.

1528
01:14:56,155 --> 01:14:57,740
Come on out and fight!

1529
01:15:00,284 --> 01:15:03,078
Were you in love with her,
Beast?

1530
01:15:03,120 --> 01:15:05,789
Did you honestly think
she'd want you

1531
01:15:05,830 --> 01:15:08,124
when she had someone like me?

1532
01:15:18,550 --> 01:15:21,094
lt's over, Beast.

1533
01:15:21,094 --> 01:15:22,804
Belle is mine!

1534
01:15:27,976 --> 01:15:29,561
Let me go. Let me go.

1535
01:15:29,602 --> 01:15:31,270
Please, don't hurt me.

1536
01:15:31,312 --> 01:15:32,271
l'll do anything.

1537
01:15:32,313 --> 01:15:33,856
Anything!

1538
01:15:46,743 --> 01:15:49,370
Get out.

1539
01:15:49,412 --> 01:15:51,497
Beast!

1540
01:15:51,539 --> 01:15:52,665
Belle?

1541
01:16:00,297 --> 01:16:02,382
Belle?

1542
01:16:07,929 --> 01:16:10,181
You came back.

1543
01:16:46,756 --> 01:16:49,592
You...

1544
01:16:49,634 --> 01:16:51,219
You came back.

1545
01:16:51,260 --> 01:16:52,887
Of course l came back.

1546
01:16:52,929 --> 01:16:54,597
l couldn't let them...

1547
01:16:54,639 --> 01:16:56,474
Oh, this is all my fault.

1548
01:16:56,515 --> 01:16:58,851
lf only l'd gotten here sooner.

1549
01:16:58,851 --> 01:17:02,229
Maybe... it's better...

1550
01:17:02,271 --> 01:17:03,522
it's better this way.

1551
01:17:03,563 --> 01:17:05,774
Don't talk like that.

1552
01:17:05,774 --> 01:17:07,233
You'll be all right.

1553
01:17:07,275 --> 01:17:08,651
We're together now.

1554
01:17:08,693 --> 01:17:10,945
Everything's going to be fine.

1555
01:17:10,945 --> 01:17:13,072
You'll see.

1556
01:17:13,114 --> 01:17:16,242
And... at least...

1557
01:17:16,283 --> 01:17:18,911
l got to see you...

1558
01:17:18,953 --> 01:17:20,579
one last time.

1559
01:17:30,880 --> 01:17:32,423
No. No.

1560
01:17:32,465 --> 01:17:36,260
Please... Please...

1561
01:17:36,302 --> 01:17:38,178
Please, don't leave me.

1562
01:17:40,264 --> 01:17:43,975
l love you.

1563
01:19:17,520 --> 01:19:18,854
Belle.

1564
01:19:18,896 --> 01:19:20,522
lt's me.

1565
01:19:35,161 --> 01:19:36,787
lt is you.

1566
01:20:08,108 --> 01:20:10,401
Lumiere.

1567
01:20:10,443 --> 01:20:12,904
Cogsworth!

1568
01:20:12,945 --> 01:20:15,031
Mrs. Potts!

1569
01:20:15,072 --> 01:20:16,198
Look at us.

1570
01:20:16,240 --> 01:20:17,741
Mama, Mama.

1571
01:20:22,955 --> 01:20:24,206
My goodness.

1572
01:20:24,247 --> 01:20:26,041
lt is a miracle.

1573
01:20:36,425 --> 01:20:37,760
L'amour.

1574
01:20:41,471 --> 01:20:43,682
Well, Lumiere, old friend.

1575
01:20:43,682 --> 01:20:44,933
Shall we let bygones be bygones?

1576
01:20:44,975 --> 01:20:45,892
Of course, mon ami.

1577
01:20:45,934 --> 01:20:47,519
l told you she would
break the spell.

1578
01:20:47,560 --> 01:20:50,063
l beg your pardon, old friend

1579
01:20:50,104 --> 01:20:52,356
but l believe l told you.

1580
01:20:52,398 --> 01:20:54,025
No, you didn't-- l told you.

1581
01:20:54,066 --> 01:20:55,568
You most certainly did not

1582
01:20:55,609 --> 01:20:57,862
you pompous,
paraffin-headed peabrain.

1583
01:20:57,903 --> 01:21:00,406
En garde, you-you
overgrown pocket watch.

1584
01:21:00,447 --> 01:21:01,657
Take that.

1585
01:21:05,410 --> 01:21:09,164
Are they going to live
happily ever after, Mama?

1586
01:21:09,164 --> 01:21:11,082
Of course, my dear.

1587
01:21:11,082 --> 01:21:13,167
Of course.

1588
01:21:13,209 --> 01:21:16,212
Do l still have
to sleep in the cupboard?

1589
01:21:18,672 --> 01:21:24,594
Certain as the sun

1590
01:21:24,636 --> 01:21:26,888
Rising in the east

1591
01:21:26,930 --> 01:21:29,724
Tale as old as time

1592
01:21:29,766 --> 01:21:31,976
Song as old as rhyme

1593
01:21:32,018 --> 01:21:38,065
Beauty and the Beast

1594
